    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s strongest play for 2026-04-29 is **Lawrence Butler** (74.56), who leverages a favorable matchup against Wacha to provide our highest ceiling of the day. Despite an unfavorable eighth-spot in the order, **Butler** is bolstered by a massive 10% park factor bump and a 13% platoon advantage, making him a prime candidate for power production. **Daulton Varsho** (68.40) and **Cal Raleigh** (66.37) round out the top tier; **Varsho** is maximized by an elite SP skill matchup against Bello, while **Raleigh** earns his spot primarily through his high-leverage second-hole placement against Bradley. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (66.29) remains a foundational start, with his score further elevated by a slow-working pitcher who increases the potential for him to utilize his elite sprint speed and aggressive base-running habits.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Geraldo Perdomo** (59.46) teetering near our 40.0 efficiency floor, though he ultimately secured a start due to the premium placed on his leadoff spot against Sproat. Conversely, **Gleyber Torres** (37.91) and **Wenceel Perez** (34.23) were relegated to the bench primarily due to the high-skill profile of Ritchie (2.08 xERA), which decimated their baseline expectations and forced them well below our acceptable thresholds. We are also navigating a total washout for **Bryson Stott**, whose game was postponed, and ensuring **Will Smith** remains benched as he is absent from today's active lineup. We will continue to monitor **Masyn Winn** (40.61), who is operating on a razor-thin margin today; his matchup against Chandler presents significant risk, and any further degradation in the underlying projections will necessitate a shift in our bench strategy for future slates.",
